cwn_entry.cwn_what:
> Is there a possibility to parametrize format-strings. > E.g. I want to provide a function [print_string], that, > given an integer [i], right-aligns a string as if it was > of length [i]. But following code is obviously not > possible: > let print_string i s = Format.printf "%%is\n" i s;; > > Since "%%" is a `normal' %. But since I do not know the > needed length in advance I can not write something like > > let print_string i s = Format.printf "%10s\n" s;; > > Any suggestions?
let my_print i s = Printf.printf "%*s" i s Is this what you mean? In any case search for "*" here:
http://caml.inria.fr/pub/docs/manual-ocaml/libref/Printf.html
